  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preventing undernutrition through food and nutritional assistance for very poor households with preg</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fisrt  and sedond unconditional cash transfers
Provision of infant nutrional foods to children</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Unconditional cash transfers via vouchers during three (03) months of the lean season. This will allow households to strengthen their resilience, to cover their food needs, and prevent them from adopting irreversible damaging adaptation strategies and, and therefore focus on the activities of the farming season and the management of their livelihoods.
Taking into account the increased risks of malnutrition among children in a food crisis situation, children aged of 6-23 months and the pregnant and lactating women from the very poor households will receive infant meal and local enriched water for three months to cover their costs. basic nutritional needs.</narrative>
  </description>
